{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596217","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596217"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:11:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:11:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15399"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15399","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15399"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8090"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61864"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8090","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8090"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15399"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47310"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19630"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19777"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19941"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61864"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDiverticulitis is a common and important cause of acute abdominal pain in adults. A classification system has been devised to help stage the disease according to its severity and guide management decisions. This is the Modified Hinchey classification.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pairs of Modified Hinchey stages represents perforation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["I and II","II and III","III and IV","I and IV","II and IV"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Modified Hinchey classification for diverticulitis has four stages:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage I: Confined pericolic inflammation or phlegmon\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage II: Confined pericolic abscess\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage III\u003C/strong\u003E: Generalised purulent peritonitis from perforation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage IV\u003C/strong\u003E: Generalised faecal peritonitis from perforation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStages \u003Cstrong\u003EI\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003EII\u003C/strong\u003E represent contained inflammation, while stages III and IV represent perforation with different types of contamination. This classification helps determine whether conservative or surgical management is most appropriate.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The Modified Hinchey classification stages III and IV represent perforation in diverticulitis","Stage III indicates purulent peritonitis while Stage IV indicates fecal peritonitis","The Modified Hinchey classification has only four stages total (I-IV)"],"references":["Piscopo N, Ellul P. Diverticular Disease: A Review on Pathophysiology and Recent Evidence. Ulster Med J. 2020 Sep;89(2):83-88. Epub 2020 Oct 21. PMID: 33093692; PMCID: PMC7576390","Feuerstein JD, Falchuk KR. Diverticulosis and Diverticulitis. Mayo Clin Proc. 2016 Aug;91(8):1094-104. doi: 10.1016/j.mayocp.2016.03.012. Epub 2016 May 5. PMID: 27156370","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"ite